# Testing produces evidence, not just pass/fail

The `verify` and `review` phases require browser evidence as inputs. Every
Playwright test file in this repo must:

- Live under `tests/e2e/` and end in `.spec.ts`.
- Use the project Playwright config (`playwright.config.ts`); do not override
  `video` or `trace` locally.
- Drive a real user flow, not internal implementation details.

## Required pattern

```ts
import { test, expect } from "@playwright/test";

test("home page renders the daily brief", async ({ page }) => {
  await page.goto("/");
  await expect(page.getByRole("heading", { name: "The Daily Brief" })).toBeVisible();
});
```

## Forbidden

- `test.only`, `test.skip` left in committed code.
- Hard sleeps (`page.waitForTimeout`) — use `expect(...).toBeVisible()` etc.
- Tests that pass without asserting at least one user-visible outcome.

Artifacts land in `.sdlc/reports/{run_id}/` per `integrations.browser_evidence`.
